<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="580" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,150,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,150,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="580">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marusik, Y. M. &amp; Azarkina, G. N. &amp; Koponen, S." box="[343,585,151,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="580" pagination="101 - 148" refId="ref10349" refString="Marusik, Y. M., Azarkina, G. N. &amp; Koponen, S. (2004) A survey of east Palearctic Lycosidae (Aranei). II. Genus Acantholycosa F. Dahl, 1908 and related new genera. Arthropoda Selecta, 12 (2), 101 - 148." type="journal article" year="2004">
Marusik 
<emphasis box="[445,502,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="580">et al.</emphasis>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
split the genus into two groups on the basis of the epigynal shape, without taking into account the morphology of the male palp. This was due to the fact that males are not known for many 
<taxonomicName box="[151,390,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Mongolicosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[151,297,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="580">Mongolicosa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
; until now, about half of species of this genus are known from females only (
<bibRefCitation author="World Spider Catalog" pageId="13" pageNumber="580" refId="ref10893" refString="World Spider Catalog (2021) World Spider Catalog. Version 22.0. Natural History Museum Bern. https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 2" type="book" year="2021">World Spider Catalog 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
